<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-16T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="99" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d99">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">710.G Economic and Financial
                                Problems/13: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chairman of the American Delegation</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hull</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-16T16:00:00-03:00">December 16, 1933—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>61. For Phillips. My 46, December 11, 8 p.m. The subcommittee
                                handling topic 9(<hi rend="italic">d</hi>) must hand in its report
                                Monday. I would appreciate an urgent reply as to status of the
                                suggestion mentioned in my telegram under reference.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>